properties.areaDesc: Waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20 to 60 NM; Coastal waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20 NM; Waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL out 20 to 60 NM
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 4 at 3:21AM EST until January 5 at 4:00PM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Dense Fog Advisory, dense fog will reduce
visibility to one quarter to one half mile. For the Small
Craft Advisory, north winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt
and seas 7 to 10 feet expected.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River
FL out 20 NM, Waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL
out 20 to 60 NM and Waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL
out 20 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Dense Fog Advisory, until 9 AM EST this
morning. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 4 PM this
afternoon to 4 PM EST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft. Low
visibility will make navigation difficult.
properties.instruction:
Inexperienced mariners, especially those operating smaller
vessels, should avoid navigating in hazardous conditions.

If you must navigate, proceed with caution. Use proper fog
signals. Make sure all running lights are on. Remember to use
your radar and compass.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM EST THIS MORNING... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 4 PM EST SUNDAY
